data.title: Hole in the Wall but Mexican Food hits the spot!
data.text: You might drive by this place a hundred times and not even notice it.  Tiny and hidden in plain sight at a busy intersection but you need a good Mexican food on a budget stop in a get your fill.

data.title: Excellent breakfast at El Centinela in League City!
data.text:
My wife and I stopped in El Centinela Mexican restaurant for breakfast this Sunday morning and it was delicious!  We live in the area but have never tried this restaurant until today.  My wife ordered the El Mercado for breakfast and I ordered the chilaquiles.  Excellent and very authentic breakfast!  Small to mid-size restaurant with an amazing staff, clean facility and excellent food!  

Give this one a try the next time you are in the League City, TX area!  You will not regret it!

data.title: Great Food and Service
data.text: Loved every bit of the meal and service. I wasn't too sure About it because the parking lot was empty (we went about 3pm) but when I checked the reviews from Trip Advisor, I decided to check it out. I was completely satisfied!!!

data.title: Tasty! And never a disappointment.
data.text: I've had many dishes here and liked them all. My favorite dish: Anything with cactus! They'll usually add cactus to any dish, which greatly expands my list of favorite dishes. The dishes I usually get: Number 1, 37, 39, 44, 52, and scrambled eggs with pepper, onion, tomato, and cactus.

data.title: Great food, good prices.
data.text: My coworkers and I ordered a "paradilla" with chicken,  fajita,  and shrimp. It was tasty and fresh. Service was quick and cordial. Beer was ice cold and they had a good variety of imported from Mexico. I definitely recommend.

data.title: Mr GG and El Sentinela
data.text: Food was good.  Service was ok; need to improve the "is everything ok" check back.  The food quantity was good.

data.title: Best Breakfast tacos around
data.text: I love the genuine Tex Amex food here. The huevos rancheros makes a great brunch. Various combination plates assure that you will find something to your liking.

data.title: Best Hole in the Wall
data.text:
Best Hole in the Wall For Mexican food in League City. Our son's family took us there for a Father's Day breakfast. 

Fast service, very inexpensive (couldn't believe the prices were sooo low. The food very good and plentyful.

data.title: Good Breakfast
data.text: My fiancée and I were looking for a good Mexican breakfast place & decided to try this one. It was more than we expected- small, not busy, but the food and service were great. Not sure sometimes what to order, so tried the Huevos and Chorizo- Very good scrambled eggs & Mexican sausage with cheese and refried beans, salsa was just right. The price was very minimal and the service spot on. Will definitely try this again. My fiancée got a Breakfast sandwich on Mexican bread and was a huge portion, I even got to try some. Very good.

data.title: More Variety than Standard Tex Mex
data.text:
Located just minutes from NASA, this tidy little neighborhood place is where I go when I want something a little different.  If you want a standard Tex Mex combo platter, there are better choices close by.  But for a change of pace, try the menudo, barbacoa and machado.  And vegetarian nachos are full of flavor.  Carne guisada is always reliable, but my favorite thing on this extensive menu is #69 Grilled Talapia smothered in white cheese, spinach & cactus.

Red salsa tastes fresh and has a nice kick.  Green is even hotter, very good flavor and served in a plastic squeeze bottle.

Prices are low.  Service is always attentive

data.title: Mom & pop Mexican food that's pretty basic, but good!
data.text: No frills here, but the food is good!  The price is right, good value for what you get.  Chips & salsa are good.  Not too crowded.  Park on the side, it's too hard to get back out the front onto Hwy 3.
